\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f37\fs32\insrsid9401757\charrsid13377792 The vision which Esaias the son of Amos saw, which he saw against Juda and against Jerusalem, in the reign of Ozias, and Joatham, and Achaz, and Ezekias, who reigned over Judea. }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs44\fs16\insrsid9401757 2.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f37\fs32\insrsid9401757\charrsid13377792 
 Hear, O heaven, and hearken, O earth: for the Lord has spoken, saying, I have begotten and reared up children, but they have rebelled against me. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs44\fs16\insrsid9401757 3.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs38\f37\fs32\insrsid9401757\charrsid13377792  The ox knows his owner, and the ass his master's crib: but Israel does not know me, and the people has not regarded me. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs44\fs16\insrsid9401757 4.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 
\ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f37\fs32\insrsid9401757\charrsid13377792  Ah sinful nation, a people full of sins, an evil seed, lawless children: ye have forsaken the Lord, and provoked the Holy One of Israel. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs44\fs16\insrsid9401757 
5.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f37\fs32\insrsid9401757\charrsid13377792  Why should ye be smitten any more, transgressing more and more? The whole head is pained, and the whole heart sad. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs44\fs16\insrsid9401757 6.
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f37\fs32\insrsid9401757\charrsid13377792 
 From the feet to the head, there is no soundness in them; neither wound, nor bruise, nor festering ulcer are healed: it is not possible to apply a plaster, nor oil, nor bandages. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs44\fs16\insrsid9401757 7.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f37\fs32\insrsid9401757\charrsid13377792  Your land is desolate, your cities burned with fire; your land, strangers devour it in your presence, and it is made desolate, overthrown by strange nations. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs44\fs16\insrsid9401757 8.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f37\fs32\insrsid9401757\charrsid13377792  The daughter of Sion shall be deserted as a tent in a vineyard, and as a storehouse of fruits in a garden of cucumbers, as a besieged city. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs44\fs16\insrsid9401757 9.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f37\fs32\insrsid9401757\charrsid13377792 
 And if the Lord of Sabaoth had not left us a seed, we should have been as Sodom, and we should have been made like to Gomorrha. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs44\fs16\insrsid9401757 10.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs38\f37\fs32\insrsid9401757\charrsid13377792  Hear the word of the Lord, ye rulers of Sodom: attend to the law of God, thou people of Gomorrha. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs44\fs16\insrsid9401757 11.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs38\f37\fs32\insrsid9401757\charrsid13377792  Of what value to me is the abundance of your sacrifices? saith the Lord: I am full of whole-burnt-offerings of rams; and I delight not in the fat of lambs, and the blood of bulls and goats. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs44\fs16\insrsid9401757 12.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f37\fs32\insrsid9401757\charrsid13377792 
 Neither shall ye come with these to appear before me; for who has required these things at your hands? Ye shall no more tread my court. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs44\fs16\insrsid9401757 13.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs38\f37\fs32\insrsid9401757\charrsid13377792  Though ye bring fine flour, it is vain; incense is an abomination to me; I cannot bear your new moons, and sabbaths, and the great day; }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs44\fs16\insrsid9401757 14.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f37\fs32\insrsid9401757\charrsid13377792  Your fasting, and rest from work, your new moons also, and your feasts my soul hates: ye have become loathsome to me; I will no more pardon your sins. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 
\ltrch\fcs0 \cs44\fs16\insrsid9401757 15.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f37\fs32\insrsid9401757\charrsid13377792 
